\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 <i><Compensator-Receiver.jsfx/i> receives a reference signal on the sidechain (e.g., channels 2/3) and dynamically adjusts the levels of the input signal (on channels 1/2) to match the reference. Loudness detection by RMS and LUFS is supported. There's also a reference signal monitoring option for quick A/B comparisons.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The auxiliary plugin <i><Compensator-Sender.jsfx/i>  allows you to quickly create a route to sidechain channels.\par}
